org.openimaj.util.array

Class SparseBinSearchShortArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.util.array.SparseShortArray
      • org.openimaj.util.array.SparseBinSearchShortArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Readable, ReadableASCII, ReadableBinary, ReadWriteable, Writeable, WriteableASCII, WriteableBinary, Concatenatable<SparseShortArray,SparseShortArray>

    public class SparseBinSearchShortArray
extends SparseShortArray
    A Sparse array of short values implemented using a pair of sorted parallel arrays. The first array holds the indexes of the non-zero elements in ascending order; the second holds the corresponding values.

    Element access has worst-case O(log n) performance. Appends (where the index being added is greater than the existing indices) has O(1) complexity. Random puts have worst case O(n + log n) complexity. Complexity for getting values by increasing index for iteration through the non-zero values is O(1).

    In summary, this implementation has good access performance, and is fast for appending values, but slow for putting at random indices. It is is optimal for a scenario where you first create the sparse array and put values in order of increasing indices, and later use the array mostly for reading.

    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
    See Also:
    "http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1880804/java-time-efficient-sparse-1d-array-double"

      • unionEntries

        public Iterable<SparseShortArray.DualEntry> unionEntries(SparseShortArray otherArray)
        Description copied from class: SparseShortArray
        Provide an iterator over the union of values present in both this array and another array. Values where both arrays are zero are skipped.

        Note: the SparseShortArray.DualEntry returned by the iterator is always the same object. In addition, the iterator cannot affect the value of anything in the array (i.e. changing anything in the SparseShortArray.DualEntry has no effect on the actual array).

        Overrides:
        unionEntries in class SparseShortArray
        Parameters:

        Returns:
